HEADWORD: Homœomerical
<hw>Ho`m⟦oe⟧*o*mer"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Pertaining to, or characterized by, sameness of parts; receiving or
advocating the doctrine of homogeneity of elements or first
principles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homoeomerous</ent>⟦br⟧
